Third-party packages
---------------------
Jot for Windows depends on the following NuGet packages; each remains
under its own license:

- CommunityToolkit.Mvvm — MIT
- Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection — MIT
- NAudio — MIT
- WPF-UI (lepoco) — MIT
- Velopack — MIT
- Microsoft.ML.OnnxRuntime.DirectML — MIT
- Microsoft.AI.DirectML — Microsoft NuGet package license

Bundled binary
--------------
- FFmpeg (Assets\ffmpeg\ffmpeg.exe) — LGPL v2.1 or later. Used only as a
  decode-only fallback for audio/video file import, invoked as a separate
  process (not statically linked into Jot's binary).

Speech models
-------------
On-device speech models (Parakeet-TDT, Nemotron ASR) are fetched at
runtime and are covered by their own upstream licenses — see the model's
page on Hugging Face.
